--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
INFORMATION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Name   : docker_ce
Type   : Ansible role

Authors: liv community
License: Simplified BSD License

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
DESCRIPTION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Docker is an open-source engine that automates the deployment of any application
as a lightweight, portable, self-sufficient container that will run virtually
anywhere.

Docker containers can encapsulate any payload, and will run consistently on and
between virtually any server. The same container that a developer builds and
tests on a laptop will run at scale, in production*, on VMs, bare-metal servers,
OpenStack clusters, public instances, or combinations of the above.

For more detailed information on the usage and available configuration options
please consult the following sections.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
USAGE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

INSTALL
  - hosts: all
    roles:
      - role: docker_ce
    vars:
      docker_ce_state: 'install'

ENABLE
  - hosts: all
    roles:
      - role: docker_ce
    vars:
      docker_ce_state: 'enable'

DISABLE
  - hosts: all
    roles:
      - role: docker_ce
    vars:
      docker_ce_state: 'disable'

REMOVE
  - hosts: all
    roles:
      - role: docker_ce
    vars:
      docker_ce_state: 'remove'

INACTIVE
  - hosts: all
    roles:
      - role: docker_ce
    vars:
      docker_ce_state: 'inactive'

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
PARAMETERS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ROLE
  docker_ce_state
    Description: Control the state of the role.
    Implemented: 0.1
    Required   : False
    Value      : Predetermined
    Type       : String
    Default    : 'enable'
    Options    :
      Install : 'true' | 'yes' | 'install'
      Enable  : 'start' | 'on' | 'enable'
      Disable : 'stop' | 'off' | 'disable'
      Remove  : 'false' | 'no' | 'remove'
      Inactive: 'quiesce' | 'inactive'

  docker_ce_daemon
    Description: Define the 'docker_ce_daemon' option.
    Implemented: 2.0
    Required   : False
    Value      : Arbitrary
    Type       : Hash
    Default    : {max-concurrent-downloads: 1, max-concurrent-uploads: 1}
    Options    :
      Examples: {max-concurrent-downloads: 1, max-concurrent-uploads: 1}
      None    : {}

  docker_ce_http_proxy
    Description: Define the 'docker_ce_http_proxy' option.
    Implemented: 0.3
    Required   : False
    Value      : Arbitrary
    Type       : String
    Default    : ''
    Options    :
      Examples: 'http://proxy.domain.tld:3128'
      None    : ''

  docker_ce_https_proxy
    Description: Define the 'docker_ce_https_proxy' option.
    Implemented: 0.3
    Required   : False
    Value      : Arbitrary
    Type       : String
    Default    : ''
    Options    :
      Examples: 'http://proxy.domain.tld:3128'
      None    : ''

  docker_ce_no_proxy
    Description: Define the 'docker_ce_no_proxy' option.
    Implemented: 0.3
    Required   : False
    Value      : Arbitrary
    Type       : Array
    Default    : []
    Options    :
      Examples: ['192.168.0.0/16', '172.16.0.0/12', '10.0.0.0/8']
      None    : []

